PLEAS OF THE FOREST IN THE COUNTY OF NORTH- AMPTON ON THE MORROW³ OF ST. MICHAEL IN THE FIFTY-SIXTH YEAR OF THE REIGN OF KING HENRY THE SON OF KING JOHN, BEFORE ROGER OF CLIFFORD, MATTHEW DE COLOMBIERES, NICHOLAS OF ROMSEY AND REYNOLD OF OAKLEY, JUSTICES

ASSIGNED FOR HEARING AND DETERMINING THE SAME PLEAS.

As yet of the venison of Rockingham.
